HEADWORD: Metrosideros
<hw>Met`ro*si*de"ros</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <?/ heart of a tree + <?/ iron.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
myrtaceous genus of trees or shrubs, found in Australia and the South
Sea Islands, and having very hard wood. <spn>Metrosideros vera</spn> is
the true ironwood.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

